                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12948617" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 27 Aug 2008 06:12:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okay is fixing this now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Camel will now as before do by default: 1 regular attempt + 5 re-deliveries = a total of 6 times to process an exchange before moving to the dead letter channel.&lt;br/&gt;
Camel does this in 1.4 or older, just the counter was wrong when you was reading it from the dead letter channel after it was moved there. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12948529" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 27 Aug 2008 06:12:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also the redelivery boolean flag was always TRUE even though there was no attempt of redelivery. This is also fixed now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12949327" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 23 Oct 2008 04:37:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing 1.5 issues&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
